Class Equations

  • java.lang.Object
    • DifferentialGraphs.Equations

  • public final class Equations
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is able to interpret and evaluate expressions containing two variables x and y as well as well as many functions. This class takes a string expression as input and can check whether it's valid, format it, or find it's result given values for x and y.
    Version:
    1.0 December 26th 2015
    Author:
    Reyno Tilikaynen

      • check

        public static boolean check(java.lang.String eq)
        Checks whether an expression is properly formatted.

        For example, [check ("2sin(xypi)")] returns true, while [check ("2**3")] returns false.

        Parameters:
        eq - The string expression
        Returns:
        True if the string is properly formatted, false otherwise.
